We must determine the net fixed‐assets value as of the end of the period. In our transactions only three events affect the fixed‐assets item:

1. On “2023‑12‑31” the company initially “booked” fixed assets for 5,000,000.00.
2. Also on 2023‑12‑31 a fixed asset was purchased – a “Fixed Assets Purchase” record “FixedAsset20231231001” shows an addition of 324,677.57.
3. Then during 2024‑01‑01 a depreciation event “Depreciation20240101001” reduced fixed assets by 45,753.36.

The gross fixed assets at period end are:
  5000000.00 + 324677.57 = 5324677.57

After subtracting accumulated depreciation:
  5324677.57 – 45753.36 = 5278924.21

Thus, the “fixed assets net” item is:
 • Initial value: 5000000.00 
 • End value (after additions and depreciation): 5278924.21

Below is our answer in the required JSON format.

--------------------------------------------------

{"solution": {"fixed assets net Initial Value": "5000000.00", "fixed assets net End Value": "5278924.21"} }
